
  To get statistical information from Infranet DB one can use perl script
  db_run. This script can display a number of various statistical information
  which could be useful for DB  estimation and tuning. 
  There is a configuration file db_conf.pm which contains some parameters and 
  procedures. Check and change Oracle user, password and connection string in
  this file. We use an assumption that name of Infranet tablespaces
  begin with "PIN" and tablespaces for indexes begin with "PINX". All scripts
  bellow use one argument - " name of file " to store result.

  -a  - obtain the space information by tables (using analyze_pin.sql,
    pin_tables_stats.sql, process_stat.sh), this script is very time consuming
    and could be used for small DB.
  -r   - displays number of column fot each table ( uses sql script
    pin_profile.sql to perform count(*) for each table ).
  -s    -displays the size of each used tablespace ( uses sql
    script space_report.sql ).
  -p    - obtain statistics information about performance of
    DB( number of reads, writes, waitings, rollbacks information, occupied 
    spaces ... ).
  -h    - help, displays available options.

   Only one of above parameters should be used in the single run. Result of 
  operation stored in the current directory with name "data.lst". To redirect
  output file use the option "-f" with following file name.

  Example:
            db_run -r -f myfile

  Perl should be installed on the computer as well as Oracle client software.
  If perl is not installed in standard place you can:

      - change first line(s) in db_run to adjust path to perl;
  OR
      - start db_run explicitely with perl ( example perl db_run -r -f myfile);
  OR
      - copy perl into standard place ( or make symbolic link ).
